data.title: Austin - Downtown: Willie Nelson Blvd
data.meta_description:
In 2010, the City of Austin renamed 2nd Street as Willie Nelson Boulevard.  At the Lavaca Street and 2nd Street intersection stands the Moody Theater, which was built in the W Austin Hotel and Residences in 2011, as the new home for the PBS series, Austin City Limits, whose 1974 pilot starred Nelson.
	
	Willie Nelson (born 1933) is one of the most recognized artists in country music.  One of the main figures of outlaw country, a subgenre of country music that developed at the end of the 1960s as a reaction to the conservative restrictions of the Nashville sound, he has also acted in over 30 films, co-authored several books, and has been involved in activism for the use of biofuels and the legalization of marijuana.  A native of Abbott, Texas, he moved to Austin in 1972 and has been a constant presence in the local music scene ever since.
